reviews.review: Not without its flaws, but a satisfying end to the Skywalker saga.

A story that took 42 Years, 6 months and 24 days to tell and I loved this movie! I was there on May 25, 1977 and have read every book, comic, story, played every game and seen every tv show and could have not have envisioned a better ending.
Great ending to the franchise.  Gives the characters the impactful and developed ending they deserved.
If they added 15 more minutes on to the last jedi, then they could of gotten away with out ruining the star wars saga even more
This film is a huge sorry for the fanboys that critized The Last Jedi for being new and changing the Star Wars formula, and an even bigger FU to people whom like and enjoy film.

An action packed adventure that had a big job of completing the Skywalker saga and somehow managed to after what was such a divisive Episode 8. A few plot holes that were unfixable from TLJ and moments that will confuse most average movie goers. There were also some glazed over new canon inserted that will stir up the toxic fanbase, but overall very satisfying for a lifelong Star Wars fan. 8/10

Look, let's be honest. The Last Jedi ruined the story line. Really the actors should have walked out as soon as they read the script regarding Luke sucking milk off of that animal or the world's slowest space chase. So I blame them. This film does it's best to deal with how the Last Jedi left things. In all honestly, This film would have been better if they increased the running time so they didnt have to cram in Star Wars the last jedi wrap up which is basicly like a third of the film. Frankly, I think JJ did the best he could and it worked. Honestly I was hoping they would scrap the last jedi and just have Rey wake up like it was all a dream. We all love Stsr Wars and I m sure by the next one we will fell better and realize that all things considered. JJ once again pulled it off. Which he did, so go see it.

What a rotten way to end the saga. Avoid at all costs, Star Wars fans.
Even those who loved the sequel films - you will still hate it.
There is nothing redeemable about this talentless piece of lazy fanfiction.

Star Wars has become something that people seem to have unrealistic expectations over. Nostalgia seems to blind people to the hate that the PT and OT received, the Sequel Trilogy is receiving the same treatment as before. 

RoS is nothing groundbreaking, it is a bit faced paced and definitely would have been improved through some form of set up in TLJ, however, it gives you everything you want from a star wars movie and thats why it's good. 

If anyone sits down to microanalyse this movie, it will be full of flaws and plotholes, but if you're after a movie that you can sit down and enjoy? This is definitely one of them
